<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910509-0070</DOCNO><DOCID>910509-0070.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Lotus Development Corp.:   Software Firm Is Shipping   Updated Version of 1-2-3</HL><DATE>05/09/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7</SO><CO>   LOTS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)</RE><LP>   Lotus Development Corp., Cambridge, Mass., said it beganshipping Release 2.3 of its 1-2-3 computer spreadsheetprogram, an updated version of the program that it saidincludes enhanced &quot;graphical and analytic&quot; capabilities.   The updated program will be available in retail storesnext week, the maker of personal-computer software said. Thesuggested retail price of a standard version is $495.</LP><TEXT>   Lotus also said it introduced 1-2-3 Release 3.1+, anupdate of the 3.1 version of its 1-2-3 program. The suggestedretail price of a standard version of the 1-2-3 Release 3.1+program will be $595. The program will be available within 60days, the company said.</TEXT></DOC>